post.body:
@nofish Man, I've got an idea, and I think, mlst people will agree with me: Like in other social networks, here people should see posts starting with their nickname in activity feed (since there are no other notifications) even if they don't follow the person writing to them. (see "Mentions" on Twitter/Twister).

Without it I have just had to go to my profile and check my old posts to see if anyone who I don't follow wrote anything.

Another problem is for this reason that I start following people that are not very interesting for me (but I still want to see when they answer me).

Cool... I had an unchanging amount of NXT for a month or so and still I can't forge. Cool. Very fucking cool.

I don't really want to forge very much, but it's PoS system, and what's the point if I can't proove my stake?? And what's more importantly is wether or not I will be given Ardor after all this?..

@ks, could you please check my account? Do you also see zeros on the amount that is needed for forging? It just can't be so!

comment.body:
@Mynameislegion: just follow me. I'll write a post here or in my blog, when I'm ready.

Currently I could launch several preinstalled apps on several VMs. And I can say, it was good. A browser, software center, 2 terminals (all in a separate VM) + 2 default VMs were about 1.5GB RAM and 0% CPU when loaded and left alone. Supercool if to comtare to what I saw on VirtualBox.

BUT all those machines were linux, 1 Ubuntu and several Fedoras, so it did not impress me much. If I could launch MacOS and Windows the same way - that would be really impressive. Would I be able to play games on it - would be super-super-cool. But I don't expect that to happen =D
